    en: "Carpet wears out. A New York landlord cannot charge a tenant for carpet that wore from normal use. Apartment-grade carpet has a typical useful life of 5 to 10 years. If the carpet was already old at move-in and is worn at moveout, that is normal wear and tear — not damage. But stains that will not clean, burns, pet damage, and large tears are different. The main statute is General Obligations Law 7-108. A security deposit deduction for carpet has to match real damage, weighted by how much useful life was left."
